5. Recency Bias

The tendency to overweigh the most recent information and events.

‚Ä¢ Causes traders to lose sight of the bigger picture

‚Ä¢ #BTC up 7,000% in the past 5 years.

  Then it down 30.03% in the last 3 months.

  You think #BTC loses its worth.

=> Zoom out

2. Anchoring bias

The tendency to over-rely on the first information you have.

‚Ä¢ Caused by human‚Äôs need to make estimates

‚Ä¢ You bought #BTC at $1,000.

  #BTC surge to $10,000 is too expensive in your head.

=> Evaluate purchases based on a token‚Äôs potential, not its past

1. Unit bias

The preference to buy a whole unit of a token rather than a fraction of it.

‚Ä¢ Leads to over-rating a token‚Äôs price over its value

‚Ä¢ Drives the recent explosion of meme coins

‚Ä¢ 1 #DOGE > 0.01 #BTC

=> Evaluating a token based on its merits, not prices
